python version used = 3.11.5
pip3 version used = 23.3.2

### Installation

1. Clone the repository: (Or Directly download it )

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Chhupten/hotel_booking_system.git

2. Navigate to the project directory 
    cd hotel_booking_system

3. Create and activate a virtual environment
    # On Windows:
    .\venv\Scripts\activate
    # On macOS/Linux:
    source venv/bin/activate

4. Install project dependencies
    pip3 install -r requirements.txt

5. Run the Django development server
    python3 manage.py runserver


## Accessing the Django Admin Interface

Once the development server is running, you can access the Django admin interface by opening your web browser and navigating to:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/

If you have customized the development server settings or if the port is different, adjust the URL accordingly.

**Credentials for Superuser:**

- Username: cdt or cdt@gmail.com
- Password: 12345

Superuser: Can delete bookings from other users, create and delete room categories This will ultimately lead to superuser having control over availability of diffrent categories of rooms.

Superuser can also do other admin related stuffs for example adding/delete other user and editing their roles from super user to normal users, etc.

Note: Make sure the development server is running (`python3 manage.py runserver`) before attempting to access the admin interface.

**Credentials for normal user**

